1.What is reverse-i-search in a Linux terminal?
    Basically reverse-i-search is used for to see the all the commands previously executed or entered.
    By using up arrow, we can shift the previously executed commands.

2.How do you list out the hidden directories using Linux command line tool?
    ls -a

